## Phase 1: Browser Optimization (Memory Reduction)
**Goal: Reduce per-account RAM from ~250MB → ~80MB**

### [MODIFY] [playwright-manager.js](file:///c:/Users/heyyt/Downloads/github/fb-ids-messenger/desktop/services/playwright-manager.js)

Add lean launch flags to every `launchPersistentContext` call:
```javascript
const LEAN_ARGS = [
    '--disable-blink-features=AutomationControlled',
    '--no-sandbox',
    '--disable-infobars',
    '--disable-gpu',                        // No GPU needed for headless monitoring
    '--disable-dev-shm-usage',              // Prevent /dev/shm OOM crashes
    '--disable-background-networking',       // Stop background sync draining CPU
    '--disable-background-timer-throttling', // Keep JS timers on time
    '--disable-backgrounding-occluded-windows',
    '--disable-renderer-backgrounding',
    '--disable-extensions',
    '--disable-translate',
    '--disable-spell-check',
    '--disable-features=TranslateUI,BlinkGenPropertyTrees',
    '--no-first-run',
    '--no-default-browser-check',
    '--memory-pressure-off',
    '--blink-settings=imagesEnabled=false',  // Disable image loading (huge savings)
    '--js-flags=--max-old-space-size=96',   // Cap V8 heap at 96MB per browser
];
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> `imagesEnabled=false` means profile pictures won't load in the browser, but the Messenger sidebar TEXT (sender name, preview) still loads fine. Message detection is entirely text-based so this is safe.

