## Phase 2: Staggered Polling with Concurrency Cap
**Goal: Prevent 30 simultaneous polls from spiking CPU**

### [NEW] `desktop/services/poll-scheduler.js`

Instead of every account polling on its own 2s interval simultaneously, a central scheduler staggers them:

```
Account 1: poll at t=0s, t=2s, t=4s...
Account 2: poll at t=67ms, t=2067ms...  (stagger = 2000ms / 30 accounts = 67ms apart)
Account 3: poll at t=133ms...
```

Uses `p-limit` (free: `npm i p-limit`) to cap concurrent polls at 10 at any time:
```javascript
const pLimit = require('p-limit');
const limit = pLimit(10); // max 10 concurrent Playwright evaluations
```

### [MODIFY] [message-monitor.js](file:///c:/Users/heyyt/Downloads/github/fb-ids-messenger/desktop/services/message-monitor.js)
- Export an `attachWithScheduler(page, accountId, scheduler)` function
- Scheduler calls poll functions in staggered order instead of each account using its own `setInterval`

---

## Phase 3: Process-Level Isolation (Crash Protection)
**Goal: One account crash doesn't kill all accounts**

### Architecture: AccountWorker per-account child processes

```
main.js (orchestrator)
  ├── AccountWorker (child_process): acc_001
  ├── AccountWorker (child_process): acc_002
  ├── AccountWorker (child_process): acc_003
  ...
  └── TelegramBot (main process, handles all replies)
```

Each worker:
- Manages exactly 1 Playwright browser
- Sends `new-message` events to parent via `process.send()`
- Restarts automatically if it crashes (via `cluster` or `child_process` with respawn logic)
- Main process collects all events and forwards to Telegram

**Libraries:**
- Node.js built-in `child_process` — spawn workers (free, built-in)
- `pino` — structured logging per worker (free: `npm i pino`)

### [NEW] `desktop/workers/account-worker.js`
```javascript
// Runs as a child process. Manages one FB account.
// Reports messages back to parent with process.send()
const accountId = process.env.ACCOUNT_ID;
// ... init playwright, message monitor, heartbeat
process.on('message', (msg) => {
    if (msg.type === 'reply') handleReply(msg);
});
```

### [MODIFY] [desktop/main.js](file:///c:/Users/heyyt/Downloads/github/fb-ids-messenger/desktop/main.js)
- Spawn workers instead of in-process account management
- Respawn crashed workers with exponential backoff

