## Phase 4: Persistent Reply Queue (Survive Crashes)
**Goal: Replies queued for delivery survive app restarts**

### Option A: File-based queue (simplest, no extra services)
Use `better-queue` (free: `npm i better-queue`):
```javascript
const Queue = require('better-queue');
const replyQueue = new Queue(async (task, cb) => {
    await executeReply(task);
    cb(null);
}, {
    store: { type: 'sqlite', path: './queue.db' }, // persists to disk
    concurrent: 1, // one reply per account at a time
    retries: 3,
    retryDelay: 5000
});
```

### Option B: bullmq + Redis (if you have Redis installed)
More powerful — distributed, retry policies, dead-letter queue, dashboard UI:
```javascript
const { Queue, Worker } = require('bullmq');
const replyQueue = new Queue('replies', { connection: redisClient });
```

**Recommendation: Start with Option A (no dependencies), upgrade to Option B when scaling beyond 30 accounts.**

---

## Phase 5: Session Keep-Alive Heartbeat (30-Day Sessions)
**Goal: Keep Facebook sessions alive for 30+ days without re-login**

Facebook sessions expire because cookies like `xs` have a rolling expiry — they refresh on activity. A browser that stays idle for 7+ days will get its session killed.

### [MODIFY] [session-monitor.js](file:///c:/Users/heyyt/Downloads/github/fb-ids-messenger/desktop/services/session-monitor.js)
Change the keep-alive from passive sidebar check to **active heartbeat**:

```javascript
async _heartbeat(acc, page) {
    // 1. Navigate to Messenger (refreshes rolling session cookies)
    // Every 4 hours, do a proper page.reload() to renew session tokens
    const hoursSinceReload = (Date.now() - (acc._lastReload || 0)) / 3600000;
    if (hoursSinceReload > 4) {
        await page.reload({ waitUntil: 'domcontentloaded', timeout: 20000 });
        acc._lastReload = Date.now();
        return;
    }
    
    // 2. Every 10 min: lightweight JS evaluation (no reload needed)
    // Just verifying FB is alive — generates a minimal activity signal
    await page.evaluate(() => {
        // Trigger a tiny XHR that looks like normal browser activity
        // This refreshes the session without a full page reload
        fetch('/ajax/webstorage/process_queue/?ajax=1', { 
            credentials: 'include',
            headers: { 'X-FB-Friendly-Name': 'WebStorageProcessQueue' }
        }).catch(() => {}); // silently ignore errors
    });
}
```

### Session Persistence Strategy
| Timeframe | Action | Expected Result |
|-----------|--------|-----------------|
| Every 10 min | Lightweight JS ping | Session tokens refreshed |
| Every 4 hours | Page reload | Full cookie renewal |
| Every 24 hours | Navigate away + back | Forces full session re-auth |
| 7+ days idle | Alert user | May need re-login anyway |

With this, sessions should survive **30+ days** without manual re-login, as long as Facebook doesn't force a checkpoint (2FA/suspicious activity).

